        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 12:58PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 1258 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
over Sedalia, or 18 miles south of Denver, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated. Dry microbursts are possible over the next
30 minutes.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eastern Denver, southwestern Aurora, Centennial, Highlands Ranch,
Castle Rock, Parker, eastern Littleton, southern Englewood,
Greenwood Village, Lone Tree, Roxborough Park, The Pinery, Castle
Pines, Franktown, Arapahoe Park, Ponderosa Park, Sedalia, Buckley
SFB, Louviers and Cherry Hills Village.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
